comments.body:
There were some additional synchronization issues which arose which required the following:

```sql
update workflowitem set state=3 from (select w.item_id from metadatavalue as v inner join workflowitem as w on v.resource_id=w.item_id  where v.text_value like '%Final published version.%' and w.state=3) as subquery where workflowitem.item_id=subquery.item_id;
```

As reported by Hannah, this database update alone was not sufficient, as the following was discovered:

> There are two records that were in Yuan's task pool which have retained the "Initial Review" Label. Here are the titles... This first one should be "Needs Reviewed" see: Individual and Combined Roles of the Master Regulators AphA and LuxR in Control of the Vibrio harveyi Quorum-Sensing Regulon. This second one should be "Reviewed" see: Phase locking of a semiconductor double-quantum-dot single-atom maser
Liu, Y-Y; Hartke, TR; Stehlik, J; Petta, Jason R.

I am finding the following in response to a database query:

```sql
select workflow_id,item_id,collection_id,state,owner from workflowitem where state=1;
 workflow_id | item_id | collection_id | state | owner
-------------+---------+---------------+-------+-------
        2663 |    2763 |            51 |     1 |
        1476 |    1578 |            46 |     1 |
```

princeton_ansible.title: Add a tag to nginxplus role for certificates
Figgy playbook fails to mount shared resources

comments.body: As @kayiwa was describing, this may well be related to the potential issues which arise due to perceived DDOS attacks upon the OIT DNS servers (this is due to the number of requests made, frequently, by `figgy` servers).

Ah, thanks @jrgriffiniii and @kayiwa for the background. Since the existing figgy machines are set to 127.0.0.53, we're clearly not mimicking DDOS attacks on OIT any more. I'll open a PR to update the bind9 role for future VM builds.
